{
  "topic": "DeFi TVL by blockchain over time",
  "summary": "Total DeFi Total Value Locked (TVL) grew from ~$15B at end-2020 to an all-time high of ~$177B on 9 Nov 2021, then collapsed to ~$38B by end-2022 during the bear market (Terra/Luna, FTX). It recovered to ~$53B (end-2023), surged to ~$117B (end-2024), held ~$114B at end-2025, and as of mid-June 2026 sits around $74.5B amid a 2026 drawdown. Ethereum has always dominated DeFi TVL: ~96% in 2020, falling to ~57% by end-2021 as alt-L1s (BSC, Solana, Avalanche, Polygon) rose, and oscillating in a ~53-60% band since. As of 16 Jun 2026, Ethereum holds ~$39.8B (~53% dominance, near multi-year lows). The next tier is now tightly bunched and specialized: BSC ~$5.3B (DEX flow), Solana ~$4.9B, Tron ~$4.6B (stablecoin settlement), Bitcoin DeFi ~$4.3B (BTCFi, new in 2024), and Base ~$4.3B. Newer entrants Hyperliquid (~$1.65B, perps) and Plasma (~$0.73B) have climbed fast. Arbitrum (~$1.3B), Polygon (~$1.05B), Avalanche (~$0.48B) and Sui (~$0.45B) have faded from their prior peaks. All values are USD billions. Primary source: DefiLlama API (api.llama.fi), which methodology aggregates protocol TVL per chain; figures are point-in-time and excludes double-counted/staking depending on toggle.",
